4.10	Stereotactic_radiosurgery	Stereotactic surgery	Stereotactic surgery or stereotaxy (not to be confused with the virtuality concept of stereotaxy) is a minimally invasive form of surgical intervention which makes use of a three-dimensional coordinate system to locate small targets inside the body and to perform on them some action such as ablation, biopsy, lesion, injection, stimulation, implantation, radiosurgery (SRS) etc.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/08/Brain_biopsy_under_stereotaxy.jpg/220px-Brain_biopsy_under_stereotaxy.jpg
